SerializableUser

                           java.lang.String name)

Constructs a session-persistent user that is stored via the Serializable interface. Once this user is constructed, his or her unique user id is immutable.

Parameters:
id - short string that uniquely identifies this user
name - full name of this user
Throws:

getAppointments

public java.util.SortedSet<Appointment> getAppointments()
Description copied from class: User
Returns a collection that contains all of appointments that this user is attending, sorted in their natural order. Appointments are in natural order when they are sorted in ascending order in the following priority: beginning, end, location, and description.
